        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 28 at 5:50PM MDT by NWS Billings MT</headline>
        <description>At 550 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Fromberg, or 24 miles northeast of Red Lodge, moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Joliet, Fromberg, Pryor, Edgar and Crow Indian Reservation.

This does not include the city of Billings.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
